.TH ANT 1 "2026-06-19" "ant 1.0" "~ANT Manual"
.SH NAME
ant \- distributed version control written in ~ATH
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ant
.I command
.RI [ args... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ant
is a colony-themed version control system written in the ~ATH esoteric
language. It tracks files as snapshots in chambers (commits), organized
by tunnels (branches). Remote storage is provided by a ~colony server.
.PP
All state lives in
.B .ant/
at the working directory root.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Initialization
.TP
.B ant hatch
Initialize a new colony. Creates the
.B .ant/
scaffold with HEAD pointing to
.IR main ,
empty forage pile, chamber storage, and id counter. Aborts if
.B .ant
already exists.
.SS Staging and Committing
.TP
.BI "ant collect " file
Stage a file to the forage pile for the next commit. Prints a warning
if the file is already staged.
.TP
.BI "ant dig " "message " [ name ]
Commit all foraged files into a new chamber. Allocates a chamber id,
stores each staged file as a numbered blob, writes the manifest, updates
the current tunnel ref, and clears the forage pile. Aborts if the
forage pile is empty. If
.I name
is given, the chamber is tagged with that name for later reference.
.SS History
.TP
.B ant log
Walk chamber history backwards from HEAD to root.
Prints chamber id, optional name, and commit message.
.TP
.B ant trail
Display colony history as a column-based ASCII graph, newest first.
Renders commits, splice merges, and fission forks with column connectors.
.TP
.B ant status
Show current tunnel name, forage pile contents, and modified or deleted
files relative to the HEAD chamber. Prints "working tree clean" if
nothing has changed.
.TP
.B ant diff
Line-by-line diff of working tree files against the HEAD chamber snapshot.
Marks deleted files. Exits early if no chambers exist.
.SS Branching
.TP
.B ant fission
List all tunnels. The current tunnel is marked with
.BR * .
.TP
.BI "ant fission " name
Create a new tunnel at the current HEAD. Does not switch to it.
.TP
.BI "ant fission " "name ref"
Create a new tunnel at chamber
.IR ref ,
switch HEAD to it, clear the forage pile, and restore the working tree.
.I ref
may be a numeric chamber id or a chamber name set by
.BR dig .
.TP
.BI "ant tunnel " name
Switch to an existing tunnel. Updates HEAD and restores the working tree
from the tunnel's tip chamber.
.SS Merging
.TP
.BI "ant splice " branch
Three-way merge of
.I branch
into the current tunnel. Walks both histories to find a common ancestor.
Per-file merge rules:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Only ours changed \(em keep ours.
.IP \(bu 2
Only theirs changed \(em take theirs.
.IP \(bu 2
Both changed \(em write conflict markers
.RB ( <<<<<<< " / " ======= " / " >>>>>>> ).
.IP \(bu 2
File only in theirs \(em added.
.RE
.IP
Conflicts are written to the working tree. Resolve manually, then
.B collect
and
.BR dig .
.SS Copying
.TP
.BI "ant transplant " "src " [ dst ]
Copy a colony to a new location. Defaults to
.IR src -colony
if
.I dst
is omitted. Copies all refs, chambers, and metadata, then restores
the working tree at the destination.
.SS Networking
Push and pull require a running ~colony server.
.TP
.BI "ant deliver " "host port colony-id password"
Push all local state (HEAD, refs, chambers) to the remote server.
First connection with an unknown colony-id registers it; subsequent
connections must match the password.
.TP
.BI "ant gather " "host port colony-id password"
Pull remote state from the server and restore the working tree.
Creates the
.B .ant/
scaffold if missing.
.SH STORAGE
.nf
\&.ant/
  HEAD          current tunnel name
  next_id       monotonic chamber counter
  forage        staged filenames, newline-separated
  refs/<name>   tunnel \(-> chamber id
  chambers/<id>/
    parent      parent chamber id (0 = root)
    message     commit message
    name        optional chamber name
    files       manifest of tracked filenames
    0, 1, ...   file blobs indexed to manifest order
.fi
.PP
Chamber id 0 is the root sentinel. Ids increment from 1.
.SH REVERTING
There is no destructive reset. Use
.B fission
to branch from any historical chamber:
.PP
.nf
ant log                        # find target chamber id
ant fission rollback 3         # branch at chamber 3
ant fission rollback v1.0      # branch at named chamber
.fi
.PP
Previous work is preserved \(em the old tunnel still points at its tip.
.SH MERGE CONFLICTS
Conflicting files are written with standard conflict markers:
.PP
.nf
<<<<<<< ours
(your version)
=======
(their version)
>>>>>>> theirs
.fi
.PP
Edit the file to resolve, then
.B ant collect
and
.BR "ant dig" .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B ant
exits 0 on success. Nonzero on error (missing arguments, no colony,
empty forage pile, unknown tunnel, etc.).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR athc (1)
